'''Bonniface''' (first name, dates and places of birth and death unknown) was an English [[first-class cricket]]er active 1790 who played for [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] (MCC).<ref>{{cite book |last=Britcher |first=Samuel |authorlink=Samuel Britcher |title=A list of all the principal Matches of Cricket that have been played (1790 to 1805) |year=1790 |publisher=MCC |page=}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Haygarth |first=Arthur |authorlink=Arthur Haygarth |title=Scores & Biographies, Volume 1 (1744–1826) |year=1862 |publisher=Lillywhite |page=}}</ref>

